in_5752114\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104akm1704707836734.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/akm1704707836734.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/akm1704707836734.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"soy1665702584828\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section dropDown\" id=\"soy1665702584828__section_d839e1_d840e1_d841e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1103128e49\">\n In a Modeled Entity\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11681e1_d11682e1_d11683e1\">When you create a modeled entity or field, the template you use defines the widget to be used for each type of component. In most cases, this is the EditBox widget but for Boolean fields, it is the CheckBox.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11684e1_d11685e1_d11686e1\">To change the widget of an entity or field in a modeled entity:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"soy1665702584828__li_d5384e1_d5385e1_d5386e1\">In the Entity Editor, select the object in the Structure.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"soy1665702584828__li_d5387e1_d5388e1_d5389e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11687e1_d11688e1_d11689e1\">In the Properties Inspector, go to the\n                  Presentation properties and for each component type, choose the type of widget you\n                  want to use.</p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11693e1_d11694e1_d11695e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"soy1665702584828__fig_w23ab1b5b1b7b3b5b1_w24ab1b5b1b7b3b5_w25ab1b5b1b7b3_w26ab1b5b1b7_w27ab1b5b1_w28ab1b5_w29ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Entity editor with entity selected, showing the drop down list for the FRM Widget Type for the entity\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/setwidgettype.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section dropDown\" id=\"soy1665702584828__section_d842e1_d843e1_d844e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1103128e85\">\n In a Modeled Component or Component\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11696e1_d11697e1_d11698e1\">When you add a modeled entity and its fields to the component structure, each object inherits the widget defined in the modeled object.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11699e1_d11700e1_d11701e1\">You can override this choice in the component. For example, you may want to use a Datepicker instead of an EditBox for a Date field.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"soy1665702584828__li_d5390e1_d5391e1_d5392e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11702e1_d11703e1_d11704e1\">In the Properties Inspector, choose the widget from Widget Type property. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11705e1_d11706e1_d11707e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"soy1665702584828__fig_w30ab1b5b3b7b1b3b1_w31ab1b5b3b7b1b3_w32ab1b5b3b7b1_w33ab1b5b3b7_w34ab1b5b3_w35ab1b5_w36ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Component Editor: DSP Widget Type</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"DSP Widget Type list\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/setwdigettypeincmp.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11708e1_d11709e1_d11710e1\">You can also add non-modeled entities and fields to a component. For fields, you can select a field template that specifies the widget.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"soy1665702584828__li_d5393e1_d5394e1_d5395e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11711e1_d11712e1_d11713e1\">In the Templates tab, select a field template and add it to the component structure or for form components, draw it on the canvas.</p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11714e1_d11715e1_d11716e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"soy1665702584828__fig_w37ab1b5b3c11b1b3b1_w38ab1b5b3c11b1b3_w39ab1b5b3c11b1_w40ab1b5b3c11_w41ab1b5b3_w42ab1b5_w43ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Component Editor: Templates Tab</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Component Editor: Templates Tab\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/rb_cpt_frm_templates.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__section_w20ab1b5b5_w21ab1b5_w22ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"soy1665702584828__p_d11717e1_d11718e1_d11719e1\">See also <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mae1704708062818.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mae1704708062818.html\" title=\"You can set widget properties in several ways—in the initialization file used by the application, in the IDE using the Properties Inspector, or in script. And you can set them in modeled entities, in component templates, in components, and in script.\">Setting Widget Properties</a>. </p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752114\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5752114\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves. In a Modeled Entity When you create a modeled entity or field, the template you use defines the widget to be used for each type of component. In most cases, this is the EditBox widget but for Boolean fields, it is the CheckBox. To change the widget of an entity or field in a modeled entity: In the Entity Editor, select the object in the Structure. In the Properties Inspector, go to the Presentation properties and for each component type, choose the type of widget you want to use. In a Modeled Component or Component When you add a modeled entity and its fields to the component structure, each object inherits the widget defined in the modeled object. You can override this choice in the component. For example, you may want to use a Datepicker instead of an EditBox for a Date field. In the Properties Inspector, choose the widget from Widget Type property. For example: Figure 1. Component Editor: DSP Widget Type You can also add non-modeled entities and fields to a component. For fields, you can select a field template that specifies the widget. In the Templates tab, select a field template and add it to the component structure or for form components, draw it on the canvas. Figure 2. Component Editor: Templates Tab See also Setting Widget Properties . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}